# My-Feedbacks Bridge — Docker build context exclusions
#
# Keeps the build context small AND prevents accidentally baking a
# local secret into the image. If you `docker build .` after using the
# bridge locally, this file ensures the wizard-generated config does
# NOT land inside the layer.

# Runtime files generated by the wizard / each request — must NEVER be
# committed to an image. The bind-mounted volume holds the real ones.
myfb-bridge.config.php
myfb-bridge.config.php.bak
myfb-bridge.audit.log
myfb-bridge.nonces
myfb-bridge.nonces.tmp
data/

# Docs are useful in the source tree but useless in the image — they
# bloat layer size and burn cache invalidation cycles on every edit.
README.md
CHANGELOG.md
SECURITY.md
EXAMPLES.md
INSTALL.md

# Web-server templates that aren't needed by the Apache-based image.
nginx.conf.example
Caddyfile.example

# Compose / docker meta
docker-compose.yml
Dockerfile        # the build itself reads it via -f, no need to COPY

# Misc
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.DS_Store
*.log
